    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Dishlike containers for holding soap, especially bathroom or kitchen accessories or fixtures; may be lidded. For small boxes or perforated globular containers used to hold a ball or bar of soap, use "soap boxes."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000042061/Webster's Third New International Dictionary (1961)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Recipientes abiertos en forma de fuente para guardar jabón, especialmente instalaciones en baños o cocinas. Para pequeñas cajas o recipientes perforados usados para guardar una bola de jabón, use "caja de jabón". </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Open houders voor zeep, vast bevestigd in badkamer, keuken of toilet. Gebruik 'zeepdozen' voor transportabele doosjes of geperforeerde houders waar een stuk zeep in kan.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
